Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and thinly
slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve
lengthways. Thinly slice widthways and put in a #large bowl{}.

Trim the top and bottom from the @pear{1} and quarter lengthways. Remove the core
and thinly slice each quarter widthways and then add into the bowl with the lettuce.

When the pasta water has come to the boil, add the @penne pasta{200%g} and boil until
tender, ~{12%minutes}. When cooked drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the pan.
Drizzle with some oil and stir through to prevent it from sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of oil in a #large frying pan{} over a medium high heat.
When hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and cook until browned all
over, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook the bacon lardons throughout.

Add the shallot and cook until it begins to soften ~{2-3%minutes}. Once softened,
add the garlic and cook stirring for ~{1%minute}. Add the @water{200%ml}, @chicken
stock powder{1} and half of the @wholegrain mustard{1}%tbsp. Stir to dissolve and
bring to the boil.

When boiling, add half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and the
@creme fraiche{99%g} to the sauce and stir to melt the cheese, bring to the boil
for ~{1-2%minutes}. Once melted and you have a smooth sauce stir through the cooked
pasta. Cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Meanwhile, combine the @honey{15%ml}, @cider vinegar{15%ml} and remaining mustard
in a #small bowl{}. Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Mix well and pour into the lettuce bowl along with the @crumbled blue cheese{30%g}.
Toss together with your hands and set aside.

Share the pasta between your bowls and top with the remaining hard Italian cheese.
Serve the salad in a #bowl{} on the side. Enjoy!